         IMO, the downfall was not enough play balancing before the game went live.  This resulted in near constant nerfs, especially to archers.   Now, some of these nerfs were needed, and some were not.  But they werent limited to one type of class, they hit just about everyone at one time or another.  I mean, nothing was balanced before the game went live.  Not PvP, not RvR, not the ability to XP, not tradeskills.  NOTHING.  It was technically a very sound game, but content wise, it was alpha.</P><P>Mythic also became very withdrawn after the game went live.  They caught a lot of shit, especially having once preached a 'No nerfs' mantra while the game was in beta.  They became a black hole, worse than Verant if you can believe that.  Stuff was promised and then never even commented on, much less delivered upon, for weeks and months.</P><P>Sayleth</P><P>And I looked, and behold a pale horse: and his name that sat on him was Death - Revelation 6:8<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
