         Worst flaw, IMO, in the game from a PvE aspect was the fact that a NORMAL, blue con mob could kill a caster in two or three swings. Four if they had a bladeturn (basically rune) up.</P><P>The ONLY chance a caster had to survive was if the group healer started a heal the instant a caster had agro. Half a second too late, and suddenly you're a corpse. Now add into the mix that most groups hunt red/purple mobs (red con or higher in eq terms) for xp, casters are just asking to get killed.</P><P>Even tanks die fast, instead of two or three hits they have 6-8 hits before going down.</P><P>And you were worried that EQ took too much pleasure in killing off players, in DAoC it's sadism.</P><P><a href="http://tru7h.org/absor/" target="_blank">http://tru7h.org/absor/</a> -  ask absor anything!<BR><a href="http://xzzy.org/ereet/" target="_blank">http://xzzy.org/ereet/</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
