         I also agree with most of what previous posters have said. I played a cabalist to lvl 30 (necro equivelant to EQ) before i quit 2 months after the games release. </P><P>The quest system was nice, and so was the low downtime. battles were very short compared to EQ. Graphics were pretty and didnt lag until you got in to RvR where 200 people would drag any system to its knees. The XP grind at first was very tolerable due to being able to group with almost any lvl, PL'ing was very easy and made bringing up your friends to your lvl fun..... that got nerfed quick.... after the nerf if you werent within 1 or 2 lvl's of your companions the XP was horrible and PL'ing was out of the question. </P><P>Casters are VERY fragile in DAoC. 2 maybe 3 hits from a lower lvl or even com mob will kill you, let alone hunting in a group where higher lvl mobs are the target (1 maybe 2 hits till dead). At least in EQ you can augment your gear twoard HP's and get buffs so you will live longer. IN the end what made me cancel my account was the XP nerf that basically made DAoC into a EQ style XP grind when they (the devs) said that that WOULD NEVER HAPPEN and the fact that casters were way to fragile and died way to much both in PvE and PvP.</P><P></P><P>Meridak Souldefiler<BR>58th Defiler of karana</P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
